Three persons members of the All Progressives Congress were reportedly killed and two others injured yesterday in an auto crash during the campaign tour of a senatorial candidate, Solomon Adeola (Lagos West). Solomon had embarked on a campaign tour of Amuwo Odofin Local Council Development Area of the state. The bodies of the victims were deposited at a mogue; while the injured were rushed to an undisclosed hospital. Adeola, in a statement by his media aide, Kayode Odunaro, mourned the victims. “It is quite an unfortunate accident. I sympathise with those injured and in hospital. I pray for the peaceful repose of the soul of these supporters of APC”, he stated. 4 APC supporters injured in auto crash Three killed in ghastly auto crash in Lagos Pre- election violence: Scores killed but none is prosecuted